column20: It would be interesting to look into the relevancy and importance of ACT/SAT score in college consideration. We can look at maybe 2021 college applicants of a university with a 60-70% acceptance rate who didn’t require SAT/ACT scores. Then we can compare the students who did and didn’t submit scores to how they did their first year of college. This can help determine how relevant the tests are vs how relevant other factors like gpa, extracurriculars, and course difficulty are when being considered for a university.

I have an interest in data regarding the types of majors that are seeing an increase in participants as well as looking at the kinds of classes students are taking and how that may impact their future decisions. I have done some work in the past with this kind of data with the department of education.
